column3:
Concept ACK. I think this might be better if implemented with a RAII approach, so you write:

```
{
    ASSERT_DEBUG_LOG("xyzzy");
    code();
}
```

and an error appears if the string wasn't found by the end of the block. See https://github.com/ajtowns/bitcoin/commits/201910-assertdebuglog for a patch. This way avoids the globals and lets you just do two asserts in the same bloc
